The columns are the correct types, but we need to add labels to our factors.



Re-factoring each factor variable within our query.census() function will add a lot of clutter, so let’s make another helper function to deal with all the factors.
While writing this function, I realized that the previous validation I did for the State is wrong. There are jumps and discontinuities in the state indices, so the list of acceptable values isn’t just 1 to 50. In this factor helper function, I’m adding a parameter which will return the levels of State for use in the main helper function.

